                "invention-title": [
                    "Wind, light, heat, hydrogen, carbon storage and energy storage integrated comprehensive utilization method and system for energy basin",
                    "能源盆地风光热氢储碳储能一体化综合利用方法及系统"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses a wind, light, heat and hydrogen carbon storage and energy storage integrated comprehensive utilization method for an energy basin. The method comprises the following steps that solar energy, wind energy and industrial waste heat energy are transferred to water in a heat energy mode in the daytime to form high-temperature water; or transferring to carbon dioxide to form high-temperature carbon dioxide of 60-600 DEG C; or after being transferred to carbon dioxide, high-temperature carbon dioxide is dissolved in water on the earth surface to form carbonated water; injecting water, or carbon dioxide reaching a supercritical state after pressurization, or carbonated water into the underground reservoir of the energy basin; and after high-temperature water or carbon dioxide in the underground reservoir is collected at night, heating or power generation is carried out. Part of the injected carbon dioxide can be retained in an underground reservoir to realize carbon dioxide sequestration. And the produced water can be subjected to water electrolysis for hydrogen production after being treated. According to the invention, wind power, photoelectricity, terrestrial heat, energy storage, hydrogen energy and carbon capture, utilization and storage (CCUS) integrated collaborative development can be simultaneously realized in an energy basin."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开了一种能源盆地风光热氢储碳储能一体化综合利用方法，包括以下步骤：白天将太阳能、风能以及工业余热能量以热能的方式换热传递给水形成高温水；或者传递给二氧化碳形成60℃‑600℃的高温二氧化碳；或者传递给二氧化碳后在地表将高温二氧化碳溶于水形成碳酸水；将水，或者将经过加压之后达到超临界状态的二氧化碳，或者碳酸水注入能源盆地的地下储层；夜晚将地下储层中的高温水或者二氧化碳采收后，进行供暖或者发电。部分注入的二氧化碳会滞留在地下储层实现二氧化碳封存。采出的水经过处理后可进行电解水制氢。本发明可在能源盆地同时实现风电、光电、地热、储能、氢能、碳捕集、利用与封存(CCUS)一体化协同开发。"
                }
            ]
